 Overview

Customer churn is a critical problem for businesses, especially in telecom industries. This project focuses on predicting whether a customer is likely to churn based on their usage behavior, account details, and service patterns.

⸻

 Objective

* Analyze customer data to identify churn patterns
* Build a machine learning model to predict churn
* Provide insights to improve customer retention strategies

⸻

 Dataset

* Telecom customer dataset
* Contains features like:
    * Tenure
    * Monthly Charges
    * Contract Type
    * Payment Method
    * Internet Services
    * Churn (Target Variable)

⸻

 Technologies Used

* Python
* Pandas, NumPy
* Matplotlib
* Scikit-learn

⸻

 Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)

* Analyzed customer distribution and churn rate
* Identified patterns:
    * Higher churn in month-to-month contracts
    * Customers with low tenure churn more
    * Higher monthly charges increase churn probability

⸻

 Model Building

* Used Logistic Regression for classification
* Data preprocessing:
    * Handling missing values
    * Encoding categorical variables
* Train-test split applied

⸻

 Model Evaluation

* Accuracy: ~80%
* Confusion Matrix used for performance analysis
* Evaluated using:
    * Precision
    * Recall
    * F1 Score

⸻

 Key Insights

* Short-term customers are more likely to churn
* Contract type strongly impacts churn behavior
* Pricing plays a major role in customer retention

⸻

 Future Improvements

* Use advanced models (Random Forest, XGBoost)
* Hyperparameter tuning
* Deploy model as web application
* Use real-time data for prediction

